on of CH$_3$CN is not possible, upper limits for the CH$_3$CN\ncolumn density are determined as $\\leq 2.4\\times 10^{17}$ molecules cm$^{-2}$\nfor W33A and $5.2 \\times 10^{16}$, $1.9\\times 10^{17}$, and $3.8\\times 10^{16}$\nmolecules cm$^{-2}$ for EC92, IRAS 03235, and L1455 IRS3, respectively. W.r.t\nsolid H$_2$O, these values correspond to relative abundances of 1.9, 3.1, 1.3,\nand 4.1\\%, for W33A, EC92, IRAS 03235, and L1455 IRS3, respectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Jul 2022 20:06:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-14"}
