hose of QGs. All\nQPSBs are matched to some SFGs, starbursts, AGNs, and QGs of similar $M_\\star$,\nenvironments, concentration indices, and velocity dispersions. A significant\nfraction ($\\sim 20\\%-30\\%$) of starbursts cannot be matched to QPSBs or QGs.\nThe implications are: (1) some starbursts do not quench rapidly. (2)\nSatellite-quenching mechanisms operating in high density environments cannot\naccount for most QPSBs. (3) The evolution from starbursts to QPSBs to QGs is\nnot the dominant path at $z < 0.2$. (4) Starbursts are not mainly triggered by\ntidal interactions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Jul 2022 12:24:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-14"}
